section.section
  a.anchor#skills
  .container
    .content.is-medium
      h2 Skills
      p
        | Throughout the years, i've been in contact with 
        strong multple 
        | facets of the IT-landscape. My 
        strong passion 
        | is in
          webdevelopment, this is because of the short iteration to optimize the product and the ability to make
          data-driven descisions. I love it when people use the product that i've helped to develop, so web and mobile are ideal!
    .columns
      /! Back-end
      .column.is-half-tablet.is-one-third-desktop
        .card
          .card-content
            .content.has-text-centered
              span aria-label="emoji" role="img" style=("font-size: 2.5rem;")  üë®‚Äçüíª
              h3.is-2 Back-End Development
              p Like in life most of the interesting stuff happens behind the scenes, this is especially true in
                development. Api's, integrations, back-ends, services, jobs, searching, storage you name it. This is
                where i'm at home.
              .section
                h4.is-4 Languages:
                .tags.is-centered
                  - ["Elixir", "Ruby", "NodeJs", "SQL", "GraphQL", "PHP", "Perl", "Scala", "Java"].each do |tag| 
                    span.tag = tag
              .section
                h4.is-4 Development Tools:
                .tags.is-centered
                  - ["VsCode", "GitHub", "Bitbucket", "Gitlab", "Git", "Jira", "SourceTree", "NaviCat"].each do |tag|
                    span.tag = tag
              .section
                h4.is-4 Frameworks:
                .tags.is-centered
                  - ["Phoenix", "Rails", "Express", "Laravel"].each do |tag|
                    span.tag = tag
      /! Front-end
      .column.is-half-tablet.is-one-third-desktop
        .card
          .card-content
            .content.has-text-centered
              span aria-label="emoji" role="img" style=("font-size: 2.5rem;")  üíª
              h3.is-2 Front-End Development
              p Back-ends need to interact with something consumer facing, so front-end development is also a large
                part of an app. Creating pixelperfect interfaces is not really my cup of tea, what i like to do is
                create functional interfaces using some sort of framework for ease, speed and consistancy.
              .section
                h4.is-4 Languages:
                .tags.is-centered
                  - ["Html", "Css", "Sass", "Javascript", "Typescript", "Slim", "Haml"].each do |tag|
                    span.tag= tag
                  
              .section
                h4.is-4 Development Tools:
                .tags.is-centered
                  - ["Webpack", "Gulp", "Grunt", "Figma", "Zeplin"].each do |tag|
                    span.tag= tag
                  
              .section
                h4.is-4 Frameworks:
                .tags.is-centered
                  - ["React", "VueJs", "Bootstrap", "Bulma"].each do |tag|
                    span.tag= tag
                  
